        "timestamp": "2019-03-24 21:41:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHi Max\n\nThank you so much for the patch to replace the AAI client with transactional client. After coming back from vacation I had to take care of a few urgent tasks internally. I noticed your patch had a +2 but due to merge conflict with other patches and dependency on my patch. \n\nI rebased my patch and squashed my patch and picked yours I was not able to push it due to the following error message:\n\nSeems like gerrit permission issue. So I squashed your patch into mine. As result of squash If you rebase your patch with the latest patch set from mine you should see no changes.\n\nMunir:so mahmad$ git push origin HEAD:refs/for/master\nCounting objects: 57, done.\nDelta compression using up to 8 threads.\nCompressing objects: 100% (42/42), done.\nWriting objects: 100% (57/57), 27.57 KiB | 0 bytes/s, done.\nTotal 57 (delta 17), reused 20 (delta 4)\nremote: Resolving deltas: 100% (17/17)\nremote: Processing changes: refs: 1, done    \nTo https://gerrit.onap.org/r/so\n ! [remote rejected]     HEAD -> refs/for/master (not Signed-off-by author/committer/uploader in commit message footer)\nerror: failed to push some refs to 'https://mahmad@gerrit.onap.org/r/so'\nMunir:so mahmad$",
